iao_definition: ['Strictly, a substance intended to kill pests. In common usage, any substance used for controlling, preventing, or destroying animal, microbiological or plant pests.']
label: ['pesticide']

iao_definition: ['Any condition in which the main influencing factor is a substance having a specific molecular composition obtained by or used in a reaction involving changes to atoms or molecules.']
label: ['chemical']

iao_definition: ['A benzoxazine that is N-(prop-2-yn-1-yl)-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-3(4H)-one which is substituted at position 6 by a 1,3-dioxo-1,3,4,5,6,7-hexahydro-2H-isoindol-2-yl group and at position 7 by a fluorine. A protoporphyrinogen oxidase inhibitor, it is used for the control of weeds in soya, peanuts, and a variety of vegetable and fruit crops.']
label: ['flumioxazin']

iao_definition: ['A role that inheres in an organism that is harvested for food, clothing, livestock,fodder, biofuel, medicine, or other uses.']
label: ['crop role']

iao_definition: ['A disposition of an organism to (i) undergo some bodily benefit that (ii) is triggered by a planned process.']
label: ['efficacy']
rdf_comment: ['We often say in natural language it is the efficacy of the triggering planned process such as vaccination. However, processes do not have properties such as roles, dispositions, functions, qualities in BFO. And this is also not a process profile, because it is not the process of a quality changing values (determinates) over time. Nevertheless, it is natural to classify efficacies based on the type of triggering process because that is what differentiates what happens when they are realized. For example, a vaccination efficacy will be realized through different processes than a quarantine efficacy. For individual treatments, the triggering process is a treatment (as defined by OGMS).']
iao_elucidation: ['A disposition of an organism to (i) undergo some bodily benefit that (ii) is triggered by a planned process.']

iao_definition: ['An annual vine in the cucumber and melon family.']

iao_definition: ['A compound used with herbicides that reduces the effect of the herbicide on crop plants or otherwise improves the selectivity of the herbicide for weed species over the crop plant.']
label: ['herbicide safener']

iao_definition: ['a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.', 'An information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.']

iao_definition: ['A quality that exists by virtue of being a particular point in the time of a cycle.']
